In colonial Africa, American railroad engineer Robert Adamson sets out from Mombasa, Kenya, to Lake Victoria to plot out a route for Africa's first transcontinental railroad. He is accompanied on this treacherous task by Jane Carlton, whose father and fiancÃ© have both disappeared in the wilds of the African veldt, and a spunky young Arab boy, Pasha, whose slave-trader father is working with a rival railroad firm. They contend with hostile tribes, stampeding elephants and angry crocodiles.
